Description:
This one's for everyone.
Home buyers and astute investors, this beautifully presented three-bedroom home is sure to entice a host of buyers.
Placed in a premium location offering excellent access to local schools, Corio Shopping Centre, parks, sporting fields, public transport and the Princes Highway for those who commute to the Melbourne CBD. Couple that with a fresh, smart and easy-to-maintain, single-level floorplan you will be wise to call this place home.
The opportunity is also perfect for the developer (STCA).
Prepped and ready to move in, allowing the future occupant without a worry in the world. Timber floorboards underfoot team up with the sun-kissed living spaces to deliver strong contemporary notes, while a centrally located family bathroom, cook's kitchen with a stainless steel cooker, split-system heating and cooling and ducted heating accentuates its character.
Owner occupiers will enjoy arriving home to a large, grassed front yard as you unwind in the comfort of the spacious living. All bedrooms, meanwhile, are of generous proportions and fitted with built-in robes.
The private grassed rear yard caters for large BBQ gatherings, while a spacious carport with drive-through access into the double car garage are further highlights.
Call to inspect today!
Insights: 12 Rosemary Avenue, Corio VIC 3214 was last sold in 2019 and 174 other 3 bedroom house in Corio have recently been sold.

Description:
Family Comfort with Tremendous Potential!
Desirably situated in a quiet court location, this fantastic solid-brick home presents a sensational opportunity to capitalise on easy living and untapped potential. The entrance opens onto a generously proportioned carpeted lounge room with dado-panelled feature wall, while an L-shaped kitchen offers a second living/meals area. Practical enhancements include electric wall oven, separate electric hotplate and ample cabinetry. A stylishly updated bathroom features bath and pedestal vanity, while a full-size laundry leads to a generous backyard with ample room to extend. Other benefits comprise gas heating and air conditioning; detached single lock-up garage and off-street parking. This brilliant opportunity is further enhanced by its convenient location with quick access to great lifestyle benefits and amenities including shops, schools, the Ring Road and hospital.
Due Diligence checklist are available at www.consumer.vic.gov.au/duediligencechecklist

Description:
Potential Investment or The Perfect Start!
Home Owner's Comment "The home has been a terrific rental investment for us! This home was the perfect, low maintenance rental property. Located in a quiet cul-de-sac and so handy to the Ring Road and princess Hwy, the perfect investment!"
Are you looking for the perfect entry into the market or wanting to add to your investment portfolio? Then this neat home is sure to impress!
This well-presented home will not disappoint. A solid brick veneer house comprises three bedrooms with built in robes. A central bathroom with separate bath and shower with access to the main bedroom for added convenience. In addition, there is a laundry and separate toilet. A neatly presented kitchen with electric wall oven, gas cook top and plenty of cupboard space. The open plan kitchen/dining room flows through to the entertaining area. Outside you can enjoy a low maintenance fully fenced front yard area and undercover entertaining area with courtyard.
This property has the complete package with a single garage and keeping you comfortable all year is the ducted cooling and gas heating.
Whether you want to add to your investment portfolio, downsize and still have space or purchase your first home, this property is ideal. Always in demand for renters with a prospective rental return of $270 per week.
Set in a quite court and convenient location; close to schools, easy access to the Ring Road for the keen commuter, public transport and the bustling Corio shopping precinct, walking distance to Aldi, offering all the services you could want and need. In a sought-after pocket, this property should be at the top of your inspection list
Roncon Real Estate An Agency like no other!

Description:
Light and bright, low maintenance living
Low-maintenance, light-filled and modern, this charming home is perfect for anyone seeking an easy-care lifestyle. Whether you're looking to buy your first home, want to downsize or want to add a property to your investment portfolio, this home is a must-see. Inside, the floorplan offers two spacious bedrooms, both with built-in robes, plus a central bathroom with a bath and separate toilet. The kitchen is well-equipped with a gas stove, electric oven, dishwasher, plenty of storage and an island bench. Designed for entertaining, the kitchen is open to the combined living and dining space, with doors opening out to the low-maintenance, private courtyard where you can enjoy your morning coffee, while soaking up the sunshine. Central heating and a split system air-conditioner ensure year-round comfort, a single garage with remote controlled door and internal access and laundry with direct access to the courtyard complete the list of features. You are sure to love living within this neat-and-tidy property with schools, shops and the local bus stop all within an easy walk. The Ring Road is only moments away offering quick access to everything you need.
Due Diligence checklist are available at www.consumer.vic.gov.au/duediligencechecklist

Brilliant Family Home with Extra Shedding!
Placed on a massive 729m2 block (approx) in a quiet court location, this fantastic family home offers plenty of space both inside and out!

Description:
All the space you need.
Surrounded by beautiful manicured gardens on a 605m2 (approx.) block, this two-storey family showpiece presents an aspirational lifestyle of quality and versatility with its first-class features and terrific indoor/outdoor entertaining spaces.
Designed to impress this gorgeous family home simply commands your attention. From the moment you walk in, you'll be impressed by the wide entrance and a free-flowing floor plan. Offering four comfortable bedrooms, two lounge areas, central bathroom with two separate toilets, well designed kitchen and the presence of meals/family area provides a great living space for the whole family to enjoy.
Downstairs also features ample storage throughout and a huge undercover entertainment area highlights the home's functionality for everyday family living.
Stepping outside is where you will find the single car garage with two car carport and a workshop. Extras include water tank, gazebo and three garden sheds.
Positioned in the heart of Corio, it's within walking distance to all surrounding amenities including Corio Shopping Centre, Northern Bay College, public transport and easy access to the Princes Highway for commuters.
There has never been a better time to purchase this conveniently located home with all major amenities right at your door.
